On the other hand, the high number of incomplete abortions that commonly occur in Comoros should encourage education and attention to discouraging early marriage. The poor rate of hospital care for incomplete abortions increases the risk of death for many women.

Maternal Mortality Ratio

2 deaths per 100,000 live births (2015 est.)

About half of Comorian girls are married off when just 15 years and older. Practice of early marriage is politically, socially, and religiously supported. Married off at a young age, girls are not able to complete schooling and develop education. There are 41 percent of the girls in Comoros that are married before the age of 18 and 4 percent of those under the age of 15. Many marriages of young girls occur in major cities like Moroni and which makes it hard to calculate exactly the number of girls that are married in homes.
